'''''Star Wars Insider'' 74''' is the seventy-fourth issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was released to newsstands on [[February 24]], [[2004]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*From the Editor's Desk
*[[Rebel Rumblings]]
*[[Star News]] {{C|by [[Benjamin Harper]]}}
*[[Star Sightings]] {{C|by [[Benjamin Harper]]}}
*[[Best of Hyperspace]] {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
*[[HoloNet News (Insider)|HoloNet News]] {{C|by Pablo Hidalgo}}
**[[Republic HoloNet News Core Edition 15:2:22]]
**[[CIS Shadowfeed Dispatch 15:2:29 Edition]]
*[[Set Piece]] &mdash; Geonosis Hidden Hangar {{C|by [[Chris Trevas|Christopher Trevas]]}}
*[[Bookshelf]] &mdash; An Expanded Universe [[Survivor's Quest|Survivor Off on Another Quest]] {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*[[Comics Link]] &mdash; Bad To The Bone {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*[[Scouting the Galaxy]] {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet|Steve Sansweet]]}}
*[[Toy Box]] &mdash; Unleash the Animation {{C|by starwars.hasbro.com}}
*[[Action Figure Archive]] {{C|by [[Victor Wertz|Vic Wertz]] and Dan Curto}}
*[[Crossword (department)|Crossword]] &mdash; Built Ford Tough {{C|by [[Michael Selinker]]}}
*[[Star Wars Q&A|''Star Wars'' Q&A]] {{C|by Pablo Hidalgo}}
*[[The Last Page]] {{C|by [[Randy Martinez]]}}

===Features===
*"[[Prequel Update]]" {{C|by [[Jane Irene Kelly]]}}
*:<small>Producer [[Rick McCallum]] talks about how the days are getting more intense now that the first rough cut of [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|Episode III]] is coming together, and how the film's elements—like the new [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone trooper]]—are designed to build a visual bridge to [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|Episode IV]].</small>
*"[[The New Jedi Order in 100 Easy Lessons]]" {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*:<small>Here's everything you ever wanted to know about ''[[Star Wars]]: [[Star Wars: The New Jedi Order|The New Jedi Order]]'', including the key characters, the most heroic deaths, the best fights and a complete synopsis of each book in the series.</small>
*"[[Wasaka Berries and Monster Ships: Star Wars Storybook 101|Wasaka Berries and Monster Ships: ''Star Wars'' Storybook 101]]" {{C|by [[Craig Robert Carey|Craig R. Carey]]}}
*:<small>Once upon a time, young readers could choose from an ample selection of ''[[Star Wars]]'' titles created just for children. Will fan nostalgia demand a return of ''Star Wars'' storybooks?</small>
*"[[In Focus: Digital-Effects Cinematography of Star Wars: Episode II|In Focus: Digital-Effects Cinematography of ''Star Wars'': Episode II]]" {{C|by [[Ron Magid]]}}
*:<small>Going totally digital on [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Attack of the Clones'']] meant raising the bar on miniatures—and raising the temperature on lighting.</small>
*"[[Who's Who in Echo Base: The Unsung Rebels of the Battle of Hoth]]" {{C|by [[Josh Radke]]}}
*:<small>From [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] moles to medical [[Droid/Legends|droids]], the last defenders of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] stronghold on [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]] will be remembered throughout [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]].</small>
*"[[Pearls in the Sand]]" {{C|by [[Voronica Whitney-Robinson]]}}
*:<small>When it comes to tracking [[Krayt dragon/Legends|krayt dragons]], things are seldom what they seem. Watch your step.</small>

